{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reform of petitions to include creating Citizens\u2019 Assemblies at 500k signatures",
        "additional_details": "I believe this reform would increase accountability, encourage civic participation, and ensure petitions cannot be dismissed without due consideration. I think it would also be safeguarded against misuse through regional thresholds, legal review, and Citizens' Assemblies. \r\n \r\nI think the current system lacks democratic weight and that petitions, even with mass support, are often ignored.\r\n \r\nI urge the government to strengthen public trust in democracy by making the petition process more participatory, representative, and effective.",
        "background": "Add a new mechanism to petitions so at 500k signatures and 5% of voters in at least five UK regions, it triggers creation of a Citizens\u2019 Assembly empowered to deliberate, recommend policy, or call a binding referendum. Legal compliance check of the petition request before an Assembly is set up.",
